canonical:
  title: 有贈
  author: 閔思平
  language: lzh
  text: 就第年來日日閑尙驚宦海足波瀾釣魚靜坐籬邊石採蕨晴登屋上山時有野僧來問字不妨溪友與同歡愧予非是風塵吏猶未隨君拂袖還
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 有贈
  author: 閔思平
  language: lzh
  text: 就第年來日日閑。尙驚宦海足波瀾。釣魚靜坐籬邊石。採蕨晴登屋上山。時有野僧來問字。不妨溪友與同歡。愧予非是風塵吏。猶未隨君拂袖還。
korean:
  title: 어느 사람에게 주다
  author: 민사평
  language: kor
  text: |-
    집으로 돌아온 지 몇 해째 나날이 한가해도
    벼슬 바다에 물결 센 것 아직도 놀라네
    고기를 낚으려 고요히 울 옆 돌에 앉고
    날 개면 고사리 캐러 집 뒷산에 오르네
    이따금 시골 중이 와서 글자를 묻기도 하며
    시내벗과 어울려 같이 즐기기도 하고
    부끄럽네 나는 풍진의 관리가 아니건만
    어쩌다 그대 따라 소매 떨치고 못 돌아가나
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0190_010_0250&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: A Gift
  author: Min Sa-pyeong
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Years have passed since I returned home, each day dissolving into leisure,
    yet I still marvel at how turbulent the official seas remain.
    I sit quietly upon a stone beside the fence to fish,
    and when the weather clears, I climb the hill behind my house to gather bracken.
    Occasionally a mountain monk visits seeking calligraphy,
    and I delight in the company of my friends by the stream.
    I am ashamed—I am no man of dusty office corridors,
    yet somehow I have not found the courage to sweep my sleeves and return with you.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The 'official seas' refers to the turbulent world of politics and bureaucratic life.
  - key: ''
    value: The gathering of bracken suggests a simple, rustic contentment in retirement.
  - key: ''
    value: The final image of 'sweeping one's sleeves' is an idiom for decisive action and departure, implying the speaker has been unable to fully commit to the reclusive life despite its apparent attractions.
